{
  "texts": [
    "Super-resolution techniques can be employed in paleontology to enhance the resolution of OM and thin-section images, revealing previously indiscernible fossil details.",
    "DL-based Super-Resolution (DLSR) techniques (Liu et al. 2019; Ha et al. 2018; Bashir et al. 2021) utilize neural network architectures to enhance the resolution of images.",
    "This method works by training a deep learning model on low-and high-resolution image pairs, enabling it to predict high-resolution details from low-resolution inputs.",
    "DLSR application on OM and thin-section images would allow for extracting finer details from fossil images, which are often suppressed by the limited resolution of the imaging equipment.",
    "Adaptive segmentation algorithms and morphological operations, such as skeletonization, have been instrumental in extracting features from histopathology images."
  ]
}